Habitus . BL 1.9–2.2 mm , BL/BW 1.6 . Light brown, head a little darker than rest, a bit rufous. Appendages yellowish. Antenna with 3 rd segment only half as long and thick as segment 2 (
Fig. 162
).

The specimen from Coonardoo, S of Stanthorpe (
Figs. 163–165
) is very exceptional, particularly in regard to the unusually stout trigonium ending in a narrow pilose tip (not shown).

Female (presumed). Females taken together with males and resembling them have an elongate faintly visible vulvar sclerite with some longitudinal apical folds and several angular transverse folds in front (
Fig. 166
).
